132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1979
H.P. 1322 House of Representatives, May 13, 2025
Resolve, Directing the Department of Corrections to Convene a
Working Group to Examine the Establishment of a Program to
Award Earned Time Credit for Educational Achievement to Persons
Who Are Incarcerated
Reference to the Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative SARGENT of York.
Cosponsored by Senator RAFFERTY of York and
Representatives: DODGE of Belfast, GRAMLICH of Old Orchard Beach, HASENFUS of
Readfield, MURPHY of Scarborough.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Department of Corrections to convene working group. Resolved:
2 That the Department of Corrections, referred to in this resolve as "the department," shall
3 convene a working group, referred to in this resolve as "the working group," to examine
4 the establishment of a program to award earned time credit for educational achievement to
5 persons who are incarcerated. The working group must include relevant stakeholders and
6 interested parties.
7 Sec. 2. Duties. Resolved: That the working group shall:
8 1. Analyze programs to award earned time credit for educational achievement to
9 persons who are incarcerated implemented in states the department identifies as having
10 correctional systems and programming opportunities similar to this State;
11 2. Examine data on the amount of time typically deducted from the sentence of a
12 person who is incarcerated under the programs analyzed under subsection 1;
13 3. Collect any available data on rates of return to custody, recidivism or program
14 impact or successes in other states;
15 4. Gather information comparing types of sentence deductions other than the award of
16 earned time credit made available in the states analyzed under subsection 1;
17 5. Perform any other relevant analysis or collect any other relevant data; and
18 6. Recommend steps for the Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice and Public
19 Safety to advance the development of a program to award earned time credits for
20 educational achievement to persons who are incarcerated in this State.
21 Sec. 3. Report. Resolved: That, no later than December 3, 2025, the department
22 shall submit a report that includes the findings and recommendations of the working group,
23 including suggested legislation, to the Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice and
24 Public Safety. The joint standing committee may report out legislation based on the subject
25 matter of the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This resolve directs the Department of Corrections to convene a working group to
2288 examine the establishment of a program to award earned time credit for educational
2299 achievement to persons who are incarcerated and report the working group's findings to the
3300 Joint Standing Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety no later than December 3,
3311 2025. The joint standing committee is authorized to report out legislation based on the
3322 subject matter of the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
